---

<BaseLayout
  title="How We Test"
  description="Every product review on GearForLittle uses the same structured methodology. Here's exactly how we evaluate baby gear ‚Äî and why you can trust the results."
>

  <!-- Page header -->
  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border-b border-neutral-200">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
      <nav class="text-xs text-neutral-400 mb-4" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-neutral-600 no-underline">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span>How We Test</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">How We Test Baby Gear</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed">
        Every review follows the same structured process. No shortcuts, no first-impressions-only takes, no brand influence.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12 space-y-16">

    <!-- The promise -->
    <section class="bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-white">The Core Promise</h2>
      <p class="text-primary-100 leading-relaxed text-lg font-medium italic">
        "I buy or borrow every single product I review. I use it for a minimum of 2‚Äì4 weeks in real conditions before writing anything. No exceptions."
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Testing process -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">The Testing Process</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        {[
          {
            step: '01',
            title: 'Purchase or borrow the product',
            body: 'I never accept free products from brands. I either buy with my own money, or borrow from another parent who has agreed to share their honest experience. This keeps incentives clean.',
          },
          {
            step: '02',
            title: 'Assembly & first-impression testing',
            body: 'I assemble it without watching YouTube tutorials first ‚Äî if a product isn\'t intuitive from the instructions, that\'s a data point. I time the assembly and note where I got confused.',
          },
          {
            step: '03',
            title: '2‚Äì4 weeks of real-world use',
            body: 'I use it daily in the conditions it\'s designed for. Strollers go through grocery stores, airports, and rough sidewalks. Car seats get installed in multiple vehicles. Monitors run for full nights.',
          },
          {
            step: '04',
            title: 'Structured scoring',
            body: 'After the test period, I score each product against our 5-category rubric (see below). The scores are based on logged observations, not gut feel.',
          },
          {
            step: '05',
            title: 'Competitive context',
            body: 'No product exists in a vacuum. I compare it against the alternatives in its price range to give you real context on whether the price is justified.',
          },
          {
            step: '06',
            title: 'Write the review',
            body: 'I write as if I\'m explaining it to a friend who doesn\'t have time to read 10 articles. Honest about the good, honest about the bad, clear on who it\'s right for.',
          },
        ].map(({ step, title, body }) => (
          <div class="flex gap-5">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-primary-100 text-primary-700 font-bold text-sm flex items-center justify-center">
              {step}
            </div>
            <div class="pt-1.5">
              <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-1">{title}</h3>
              <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">{body}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Photo placeholders for process -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-5">Testing in Action</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
        {['Testing a stroller fold', 'Car seat installation', 'Weight & dimensions check', 'Real-world use'].map((caption) => (
          <div class="aspect-video bg-neutral-100 rounded-xl flex flex-col items-center justify-center gap-2 border border-neutral-200">
            <span class="text-2xl">üì∑</span>
            <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400 font-medium">{caption}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Evaluation criteria -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Evaluation Criteria</h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm mb-8">
        Every product is scored on five dimensions. The weights reflect what parents actually care about most.
      </p>
      <div class="space-y-4">
        {criteria.map(({ score, label, icon, description, color }) => (
          <div class={`border rounded-2xl p-5 ${color}`}>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
              <span class="text-2xl">{icon}</span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-bold text-lg">{label}</span>
                <span class="text-sm font-semibold ml-2 opacity-70">({score} of total score)</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed opacity-80">{description}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Rating scale -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-6">Rating Scale</h2>
      <div class="divide-y divide-neutral-200 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
        {ratingScale.map(({ stars, label, desc }) => (
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 bg-white hover:bg-neutral-50 transition-colors">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 text-base">{stars}</div>
            <div>
              <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 text-sm mb-0.5">{label}</p>
              <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">{desc}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What we don't do -->
    <section class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-5">What We Don't Do</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3">
        {[
          'Accept free products, sponsorships, or paid placements',
          'Write reviews based on unboxing alone',
          'Prioritize products with higher affiliate commissions in our rankings',
          'Change ratings after brand complaints or pressure',
          'Publish "best of" lists for categories we haven\'t personally tested',
        ].map((item) => (
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-neutral-600">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-red-400 flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M6 18 18 6M6 6l12 12"/>
            </svg>
            {item}
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Disclosure link -->
    <section class="text-center">
      <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm">
        Questions about how affiliate links work?{' '}
        <a href="/disclosure" class="text-primary-600 hover:underline font-medium">Read the full affiliate disclosure ‚Üí</a>
      </p>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>
